                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A single creature can wield an adjacent willing arqsheth as a free action as long as it has two free hands. Once wielded by another creature, an arqsheth can't be wielded by a different creature until the start of the arqsheth's next turn. While wielded as a weapon, an arqsheth counts as a martial ranged weapon that deals @Damage[2d10[fire]] damage; is in the laser group; has a range increment of 40 feet; and has the analog, holy, and tracking +2 traits. Strikes made with this weapon deal an extra @Damage[1d10[spirit]] damage. They don't require ammunition and have no Bulk, as they support their own weight.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.sf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Armament of the Archons]</p>"
                },
